  "text": "Chimaira is celebrating 25 years of their debut EP This Present Darkness with a whole slew of goodies. Chimaira has posted some behind-the-scenes footage of the recording process (in all its VHS-looking glory) alongside a whopping 10 live shows from the ensuing tour around the EP's release. \"25 years ago, This Present Darkness was released—a declaration of who we were, crafted in just four days with $1,500 and unrelenting drive,\" wrote Chimaira of the EP and shows. \"More than an EP, it's a testament to the grind, passion, and brutal energy that still drives us today. \"To celebrate, we've opened the vault, sharing raw, unedited live performances from the year 2000—a gritty and honest glimpse into the chaos and determination of those early days. Thank you for being a part of our journey and commemorating this milestone with us.\" This Present Darkness featured the lineup of vocalist Mark Hunter, guitarists Rob Arnold and Jason Hager, drummer Andols Herrick, and both bassists Rob Lesniak and Andrew Ermlick. Want More Metal? Subscribe To Our Daily NewsletterEnter your information below to get a daily update with all of our headlines and receive The Orchard Metal newsletter.",
